{
  "texts": [
    "Studies on information entropy normally quantify information in only one of its dimensions.",
    "This is a very serious limitation, as no single dimension can compare a spider with an elephant.",
    "Traditional studies using Shannon information obliterate the increase of novel information dimensions in an evolving system.",
    "For example, information may be present in the description in a given language or in a speci c characteristic of a system.",
    "It might be described in terms of qubits of a subatomic particle, or it might be the description of the complete genetic characteristics in terms of bits or nucleotide sequences of a human being."
  ]
}